meta {
  name: [APISIX] deny BRP read - valid JWT, invalid purpose
  type: http
  seq: 6
}

docs {
  EXPECTED behaviour once the auth-zen APISIX plugin is implemented.

  The plugin should:
    1. Extract the subject from the Bearer JWT.
    2. Build the AuthZEN evaluation input with purpose "marketing" (invalid for BRP access).
    3. Receive a deny decision from the policy agent.
    4. Return HTTP 403 to the client without forwarding to the upstream.

  The JWT payload used here decodes to:
    { "sub": "municipality-case-api", "organization": "urn:nl:gov:rotterdam",
      "assurance_level": "substantial", "roles": ["municipality_caseworker"],
      "scopes": ["brp:read"] }
}

get {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/anything
  body: none
}

headers {
  accept: application/json
  authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJzdWIiOiJtdW5pY2lwYWxpdHktY2FzZS1hcGkiLCJvcmdhbml6YXRpb24iOiJ1cm46bmw6Z292OnJvdHRlcmRhbSIsImFzc3VyYW5jZV9sZXZlbCI6InN1YnN0YW50aWFsIiwicm9sZXMiOlsibXVuaWNpcGFsaXR5X2Nhc2V3b3JrZXIiXSwic2NvcGVzIjpbImJycDpyZWFkIl19.signature-placeholder
  x-purpose: marketing
}

tests {
  test("status is 403 - policy agent denied the request", function() {
    expect(res.getStatus()).to.equal(403);
  });
}
